Please feel free to do so, George, as far as I&#39;m concerned. I will modify the ORTE code in anticipation of it by removing the arch-related calls. Should have that for you later today or tomorrow.<br><br>If it doesn&#39;t move, no harm done - like I said, I really don&#39;t need it any more, but was suggesting the move only to finally clear that abstraction break we all hated when I originally did it (apologies in hindsight). :-)<br>
<br><br><div class="gmail_quote">On Tue, Jun 2, 2009 at 9:45 AM, George Bosilca <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="mailto:bosilca@eecs.utk.edu">bosilca@eecs.utk.edu</a>&gt;</span> wrote:<br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="border-left: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 0.8ex; padding-left: 1ex;">
